        //
        // Total remaining elements: $(n-1-x) + 1 + (n-1-x) = 2n-2x-1$.
        // This must be equal to $k_2 = 2y+1$.
        // $2n-2x-1 = 2y+1 \implies 2n-2x-2 = 2y \implies n-x-1 = y$.
        // This is exactly $x+y = n-1$.
